TextBody:
Hi Marisela,

It should be accessible again. The main issue is that there are a lot of mailer items that are not delivered and they keep gathering in the server but are unable to be processed.
The SMTP settings and the alerts set on the server, need to be revised.
Let me know how you would like to proceed, set up a remote session to check it out or is it something you and the customer can handle?

Thank you,
Eduard Nut

ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000Fp6u0:ref

We request escalation on this case because there are many issues and the system down repeatedly
Subject: Netwrix Support Ticket #421121 - Appliance running on low disk space

TextBody:
Hi Marisela,

I understand your request, and before any escalation, we should have a meeting to discuss what needs to be done to stop the issues you are having.
The mailer problems are not caused by the server but by an SMTP server issue which is out of our control. We need to check the settings and the connection with the SMTP server.
Since I do not have the availability of the customer or the timezone, here is my availability for today in the EST timezone: 1 - 2 PM and 4 -5 PM
If that does not work, please send me the timezone and availability of the customer so I can set it up.
I will connect again to the server and free up some disk space.

Thank you,
Eduard Nut
Technical Support Engineer
